# Teams — Microsoft Teams CLI for Claude Code

CDP-based: **< 0.1 second** per chat read. Requires Teams launched via `teams_launch.sh`.

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. First-time setup (or after Teams restart)
bash {{INSTALL_DIR}}/teams_launch.sh

# 2. Verify connection
python3 {{INSTALL_DIR}}/teams.py status
```

## Command Reference

```bash
# Connection
python3 teams.py status                        # Check Teams + CDP connection

# Browse chats
python3 teams.py list                          # List all visible chats
python3 teams.py list -f json                  # JSON output

# Read messages
python3 teams.py read                          # Read current chat (last 20)
python3 teams.py read --chat "Alice"           # Read specific chat
python3 teams.py read --chat "Project X" --limit 50
python3 teams.py read --chat "Bob" -f json     # JSON output for processing

# Unread chats
python3 teams.py unread                        # Read all unread chats
python3 teams.py unread --analyze              # + Claude analysis (TODOs + replies)
python3 teams.py unread --limit 3              # Max 3 unread chats

# Send messages
python3 teams.py send --chat "Alice" --message "Got it, I'll take a look"

# Search
python3 teams.py search --query "SFTP"        # Search current chat
python3 teams.py search --query "TODO" --chat "Project X"

# AI Analysis
python3 teams.py analyze --chat "Alice"       # TODOs + suggested replies
python3 teams.py analyze -f json              # JSON output

# @Mentions
python3 teams.py mentions                     # Find all @YourName mentions
python3 teams.py mentions --limit 5
```

## Task Routing

| User wants | Command |
|---|---|
| Check if Teams is ready | `status` |
| See all chats | `list` |
| Read a specific chat | `read --chat "name"` |
| Act on unread messages | `unread --analyze` |
| Send a reply | `send --chat "name" --message "text"` |
| Find something mentioned | `search --query "keyword"` |
| Get AI summary + TODOs | `analyze --chat "name"` |
| Check @mentions | `mentions` |

## Output Formats

All commands support `-f json` for structured output:
```bash
python3 teams.py read --chat "Alice" -f json
# → { "chat": "...", "count": N, "messages": [{"time":"...","sender":"...","body":"..."},...] }

python3 teams.py unread -f json
# → { "unread_count": N, "chats": [...] }

python3 teams.py analyze --chat "X" -f json
# → { "analysis": "...", "model": "...", "input_tokens": N, ... }
```

## Setup Details

Teams must be launched with CDP debug port:
```bash
bash {{INSTALL_DIR}}/teams_launch.sh
```

This is required **once per Teams restart**. The launcher checks if Teams is already running with CDP and skips the restart if so.

## Common Patterns for Agents

**Check unread, then reply:**
```bash
python3 teams.py unread -f json        # Get all unread as JSON
python3 teams.py analyze --chat "X"   # Get TODOs for specific chat
python3 teams.py send --chat "X" --message "..."  # Send reply
```

**Search across a chat for context:**
```bash
python3 teams.py search --query "keyword" --chat "Project X" -f json
```

**Daily digest:**
```bash
python3 teams.py unread --analyze      # Reads all unread + AI analysis
```

## Known Limitations

- Sidebar scan shows only currently visible chats (scroll down in Teams to load more)
- `send` requires CDP session (not available without `teams_launch.sh`)
- Navigation between chats takes ~2-3 seconds (CGEvent mouse click)
- Teams must not be minimized during reads
- After Teams updates, may need to re-run `teams_launch.sh`
- **macOS only** — depends on AppleScript and Quartz (no Windows/Linux support)

